inputs:
<|im_start|>system
You are Qwen, created by Alibaba Cloud. You are a helpful assistant.<|im_end|>
<|im_start|>user
Write a python function to remove first and last occurrence of a given character from the string.<|im_end|>
<|im_start|>assistant

label_ids:
[750, 4057, 2232, 638, 1141, 69997, 1648, 715, 262, 369, 600, 304, 2088, 6901, 1141, 36715, 715, 286, 421, 320, 82, 989, 60, 621, 521, 1648, 715, 310, 274, 284, 274, 58, 15, 549, 600, 60, 488, 274, 989, 488, 220, 16, 28283, 715, 310, 1438, 198, 262, 369, 600, 304, 2088, 6901, 1141, 8, 481, 220, 16, 4999, 16, 4999, 16, 1648, 2303, 286, 421, 320, 82, 989, 60, 621, 521, 1648, 715, 310, 274, 284, 274, 58, 15, 549, 600, 60, 488, 274, 989, 488, 220, 16, 28283, 715, 310, 1438, 198, 262, 470, 274, 151645, 198]
labels:
def remove_Occ(s,ch): 
    for i in range(len(s)): 
        if (s[i] == ch): 
            s = s[0 : i] + s[i + 1:] 
            break
    for i in range(len(s) - 1,-1,-1):  
        if (s[i] == ch): 
            s = s[0 : i] + s[i + 1:] 
            break
    return s<|im_end|>

